Direct traffic shows higher purchase conversion (~42–45%) compared to Google and other sources (~39–41%), indicating stronger purchase intent among returning or brand-aware users.
Users acquired through Google exhibit lower conversion rates, suggesting weaker purchase intent or misalignment between acquisition targeting and product offering.
